data.name: beginKeywordDescription

data.name: breakKeywordDescription
data.value:
Exits the current control block or loop. If a label is specified, each encompassing control block will be exited until the label is reached. When used in a trap, it displays the trapped error and aborts execution of the script/function.
break break <LabelName>

cleanKeywordDescription
data.value:
Specifies a scriptblock that is run once every time the script/function is executed. This block is always run, regardless of any terminating errors.

data.name: continueKeywordDescription
data.value:
Stops execution in the current statement block and advances the loop. If a label is specified, each encompassing control block will be exited until the label is reached. When used in a trap, it silences the trapped error and continues execution of the script/function.
continue continue <LabelName>
